  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a complex legal issue with several key components:\n\n1. International Legal Framework\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Egmont Group international cooperation\n\n2. Key Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act (AMLA)\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n- Criminal proceeds legislation in various countries\n\n3. Core Legal Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Record-keeping regulations\n\n4. Criminalization Elements\n- Intentional concealment of illegal financial proceeds\n- Disguising origins of criminal money\n- Transforming illicit funds into seemingly legitimate assets\n\n5. Penalties\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Significant financial penalties\n- Asset forfeiture\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Professional licensing restrictions\n\n6. Regulatory Oversight\n- Financial institutions' compliance requirements\n- Government agency monitoring\n- Regular reporting and auditing\n- Mandatory internal control systems\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent financial crimes and maintain economic integrity.",
